  "text": "Therefore, we excluded these three genes from subsequent candidate gene analyses in this study. However, Narayan et al. [CITATION_1] identified PCDH10 hypermethylation in approximately 80% of patients with B-ALL. Hogan et al. [CITATION_2] found that CDH1, CDH11, and CDH13 were hypermethylated and downregulated in pediatric patients with relapsed ALL. Considering one single sample patient with a clonal expansion of a minor clone at relapse, we cannot completely rule out the impact of methylation of cadherin superfamily genes other than PCDH17 and other family genes on ALL relapse. ",
